VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'changing the features of the face as we\'ve seen in the past. Um, you know, skin textures, it adds a pretty good amount to as well. So, we\'re going to move into this to our bald guy over here. I know that\'s That\'s the thing'

[09:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that we want to focus on with skin textures, right? Um, is his bald head. But, you can see that, uh, like, you know, it adds detail in there, but, you know, not excessively so. So yeah, this is pretty great.'

[09:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Another C dance output here. This one featuring again, not Jake Gyllenhaal. I don\'t know why I just keep ending up with Jake Gyllenhaal\'s cousin here. But you know, running this through again, this was a 1080 output. Yeah, I mean it\'s'

[10:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really really pretty solid. And what I really like about this is that it\'s not the creative mode. Like this is the precise mode. So it\'s not adding in additional details. This was kind of a bunk C dance output that I ended up getting that for some reason ended up'

[10:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'adding in subtitles. And as you can see that like the subtitles clean up and you know, don\'t change characters as they might in creative mode. For my final test, I guess I can finally showcase'

