AUDIO: 'more time to play with it. I do have to say that if it is as good at being creative as precise is at being precise, I mean that that that should be a cooker. Moving on and keeping our case at 4, Kling now generates in 4K. And'

[11:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just to be clear, it\'s actually generating in native 4K. So there\'s not like a sneaky upscaler going on behind it. Yeah, I mean when you use the 4K mode, it is actually generating at 3840'

[11:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'by 2160 natively. Let\'s take a quick look at it with a Robotech Macross inspired shot that I kind of keep playing around with. They\'re never going to make the movie. I might as well just make the movie.'

[12:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now granted, you are looking at a 4K'

[12:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'output in 1080. But you know, I mean obviously what this allows you to do if you\'re you know, working in a 1080 frame or even a 720 frame, is it just gives you a lot of latitude in terms of punching in and reframing if you need'

[12:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to. One place that I do think that the 4K stuff is going to really come in handy is with I mean it\'s kind of mundane, but you know, stock travel video. Like just you know, beach at'

[12:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sunset. We we nitpick a lot in terms of performance and quality of acting and that sort of stuff. But I mean honestly for stuff like this, I don\'t think anyone\'s ever going to notice. Still go'

[12:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to a beach and shoot stuff if you want just because it\'s nice going to a beach. But you know, overall I would have to say that it\'s it\'s great that 4K is here. Will I lean on it that much? Probably not. That said, it is definitely a great option to have if you'

[13:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have a money shot that you really want to bank on. And in particular again, the ability to reframe your shot in post-production, I mean it\'s a pretty big deal. Overall, I\'d have to say that 4K in Kling is a nice quality of life'

[13:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'feature, but I know that the real thing that everyone\'s waiting for is like Kling 3.5 or Kling version 4. That said, I mean even though C dance mania has swept the entire world, I do find myself going back to Kling quite a bit. Silly'

[13:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use case as it is, I do find that their omni model does do like the me and flames or girl in the studio skits better than any other omni model. And look, I know that that\'s a pretty'

[13:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'me-centric example, but again, I do find that each of these models do have their like tailored strengths to you. It\'s just a matter of sort of digging around and figuring out where they are. Rounding out, Netflix and I line labs. I'

[13:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'line being the company that did the AI shot in the Netflix show The Eternaut, which is a very good show by the way, have released Vista 4D. This one\'s open source. So the way that this works is'

[14:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that we have this you know, source video here obviously. It turns it into essentially a Gaussian 4D point cloud. And then you can actually retarget your camera and change your shot entirely. Yeah, pretty cool. We have seen a few'

[14:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'things like this. In fact actually over on Google Flow, they\'re playing around with an experimental version for VO3. But you know, this actually looks a lot better than the experimental VO3'

[14:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'version. I\'m definitely curious to take this out for a spin and just to see how far we can push things. As we can see here in these examples, you know, that essentially the amount of camera control that we\'re moving around within the'

[14:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frame is not you know, it\'s not like a full like world labs Gaussian splat kind of thing. It\'s more about sort of reframing and moving things around. But it definitely does look pretty interesting. So as far as like the video outpainting on all of this stuff or you'

[15:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'know, essentially the video model that\'s handling the rebuild from that point cloud, it\'s actually WAN 2.1 that\'s under the hood here. So if you\'re interested in trying this out, yeah, Vista 4D it\'s available over on GitHub.'

